HEADWORD: Pyrophane
<hw>Pyr"o*phane</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Pyrophanous</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Min.)</fld> <def>A mineral which is
opaque in its natural state, but is said to change its color and become
transparent by heat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

